OL,5, A rail union has been told not to "hold
OL,6, the country to ransom" by a government 
OL,7, minister after it announced plans for  
OL,8, new strikes from Christmas Eve.        
OL,10,FWorkers at the UK's biggest rail union,
OL,11,Fthe RMT, will walk out from 6pm on 24  
OL,12,FDecember until 27 December as the row  
OL,13,Fover pay and conditions escalates.     
OL,15,FThe strike could hit travel and        
OL,16,Fcelebrations over the festive weekend. 
OL,18,FGovernment minister Nick Gibb said the 
OL,19,Funion had rejected a pay offer without 
OL,20,Feven consulting its own membership.    
